  "interpretation": "CRITICAL FINDING: On the real Ethereum transfer graph, Louvain community detection provides substantially WEAKER sybil separation than the proxy graph suggested. Key reasons: (1) Real communities are dominated by shared service addresses (exchanges, routers, bridges) that both sybils and non-sybils interact with, creating large sparse communities with ~50% sybil base rates. (2) NMI between Louvain communities and sybil labels is near zero (0.04-0.07), indicating communities carry almost no sybil signal. (3) The shared-counterparty strategy (which directly targets funding-source patterns) performs better than generic Louvain but still has limited recall because many sybils use diverse funding paths. (4) LLM sybils, which have no on-chain transaction history, achieve 100% evasion against counterparty-based detection and near-100% against all graph strategies. This STRENGTHENS the paper's thesis: even the strongest detector class (graph-based) fails against LLM-orchestrated sybils.",
